title: Personnel Appeals Board – Government Accountability Office
description: The Personnel Appeals Board (PAB) is an independent entity in the legislative branch of government that performs the combined functions of its executive branch counterparts: the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission; the Federal Labor Relations Authority; the Merit Systems Protection Board; and the Office of Special Counsel.
